			<div class="content" id="post-content-1958310">
									

<p>Wasn't the intent.</p>
<p>The intent was: the Foundation makes choices largely deemed unethical, but not because their view of ethics is different, but because their view of scope is different. At most, the average person makes a choice that affects the handful of people nearest them, with leaders making choices for countries and so on. The Foundation has to look, literally, for what good benefits all people, or most people, of <em>every</em> country, and therefore the definition of ethics is difficult to ascertain. Essentially, until you walk a mile in another's shoes&#8230;</p>
<p>But to each their own. Thanks for the feedback at least.</p>

