			<div class="content" id="post-content-1958902">
									

<p>Agreed. This story isn't bad. I like the dialogue. But the flow of it was very predictable.</p>
<p>I think there are more interesting ethical conflicts to explore. In this context, for example, the &quot;inquisitors&quot; could challenge Foundation ethics by attacking the underlying axioms. There are plenty of entities that the Foundation contains by very &quot;cruel&quot; means which are the only way to keep it contained - but that could be <em>destroyed</em> much more &quot;humanely&quot;.</p>

