														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1958919">
									

<p>I agree that this is basically about the debate between utilitarism and deontologogy but this can be said of nearly every problem concerning ethics. It's not that easy to derail from this axis as you call it, because there simply aren't any other systematic theories of ethic that would be applicable in any way to the Foundations doing. At least, I don't know of any.</p>
<p>On a sidenote I think it could be possible to justify Foundation ethics from a deontologists point of view, too.</p>

