														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1958968">
									

<p>There are plenty of other ethical problems. Deontology and utilitarianism aren't even necessarily in conflict. More strictly speaking it's usually deontology and consequentialism that are in conflict, and utilitarianism happens to be the most common form of consequentialism. But there's plenty of other ethical perspectives and axes; virtue ethics is relatively rare right now but has been historically quite important; there's absolutism vs. non-absolutism, objectivism vs. subjectivism, motive-agnostic vs. motive-conscious ethics&#8230;</p>

