		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,1965910)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-1965910">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/synaesthesia" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1778803); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1778803&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163898" alt="Synaesthesia" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1778803)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/synaesthesia" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1778803); return false;" >Synaesthesia</a></span> <span class="odate time_1392291608 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Feb 2014 11:40</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1965910">
									

<p>Opinion: I think there's a difference between the study/discussion of ethics and moral philosophy in theory space, that is the space of all theoretical discussion on ethics by moral philosophers etc., and applied ethics, or the application of ethics in actual practice by organizations and other bodies composed of multiple individuals with stated goals.</p>
<p>In theory it's difficult or impossible to say what ethical paradigm is best, but ethics as applied within organizations is usually grounded in the practical goals of the body. One may subscribe to Kantian ethics and believe the Montauk Procedure is morally reprehensible regardless of consequence, and thus the protagonist of this tale is espousing nonsense about how his utilitarian philosophy is superior to whatever paradigms other bodies or individuals may believe to be correct. However, the stated goal of the Foundation is the protection of all humanity from the paranormal - implicitly this means that this goal is held to be the ultimate virtue by the Foundation. Within this framework, the ethics committee works to ensure that procedures do not overstep the bounds of what is necessary - it is not an organization for discussing the merits of moral philosophical paradigms in theory space.</p>

							</div>

								
